  "prompt": "How do I verify my Twitter account?",
  "response": "To verify your Twitter account (get the blue checkmark), follow these steps:\n\n1. Eligibility requirements:\n- Must have a complete profile\n- Be active on Twitter\n- Have a profile photo and confirmed email address\n- Meet Twitter's verification guidelines\n\n2. Current verification process (as of 2023):\n- Subscribe to Twitter Blue (paid verification service)\n- Pay a monthly fee (pricing varies by platform)\n- Verify your account through the Twitter Blue subscription\n\n3. Alternative ways to potentially get verified:\n- Be a notable public figure\n- Have significant public impact\n- Work in government, journalism, or activism\n- Be extensively covered in verified media outlets\n\n4. Steps to apply:\n- Go to Twitter settings\n- Select \"Verification\"\n- Complete profile information\n- Submit required documentation if applicable\n\nNote: Twitter's verification policies have changed frequently, so check their current guidelines for the most up-to-date information.",
